data.description:
This updated end unit features a main floor primary suite that has been remodeled to the highest level of craftsmanship and expertise by the builder/owner. The main level offers a beautiful deck that overlooks a stunning treed green space. Upon entering, you will be greeted by a vaulted ceiling living area with pre-finished engineered wood floors. The main level also includes a vaulted primary suite with a private bathroom featuring tasteful finishes and a walk-in closet. This suite offers ample space for a King size bed, side tables, and additional furniture. 
The kitchen is bright and airy, equipped with newer stainless steel Kitchenaid appliances. The countertops are made of Quartz and the cabinets are soft-close, complete with pull-out slide shelving. Additionally, there is a convenient standing pantry with pull-out shelves. The upper area of the home features a spacious and private office with an open view of the main floor. Down the hall, you will find another bedroom suite with a walk-in closet. 
The walk-out basement includes a 3/4 bath and a large bedroom. The living area in the basement is perfect for entertaining, featuring a media wall and a wet bar. The owner has spared no expense in updating the home, including premium flooring, carpets, custom up-down window treatments, fixtures, custom lighting, and even a duct fan for efficient heat transfer on longer runs. The attention to detail and quality workmanship is evident throughout the home. The walk-out basement also offers a covered patio that is hot tub ready, and the patio is enclosed for added privacy. 
The homeowners association provides excellent coverage of the community and is led by exceptional leadership. This location is just steps away from the Highline Canal, and the bus for the Cherry Creek school district picks up at the top of the street. Retail options are conveniently located in the immediate area. Quick access to C-470 allows for easy travel to the Denver Tech Center and I-25.
